- Warm, editorial, "creative desktop" aesthetic — soft and approachable, not corporate-dark
- Color palette:
  - Background: warm cream/off-white (#F1EBE0)
  - Primary text: deep espresso brown (#2B211A), used instead of pure black
  - Accent: dusty slate blue (#7C9BB0) for buttons, links, highlights, icons
  - No pure white, no pure black anywhere — keep everything warm and muted
- Typography: pair two contrasting display styles for section headers —
  - An elegant italic serif/script for accent words (e.g. name or tagline fragment)
  - A bold, heavy grotesque sans for the dominant word/headline
  - Small uppercase letter-spaced labels as section eyebrows (e.g. "PROJECTS", "SKILLS")
- Layout: loose, natural asymmetry rather than rigid grid alignment for the project cards — like scattered desktop icons/folders, but still readable and scannable on scroll
- Shape language: soft rounded rectangles throughout (cards, buttons, image containers) echoing a "folder" motif
- Imagery: project thumbnails styled like small polaroid/index cards with a caption line underneath, subtle drop shadow, slight rotation on hover
- Micro-interactions: cursor-follow or hover-lift effects on project cards for a tactile, human feel (Framer Motion)
- Generous whitespace — low visual density, nothing crowded
- Light mode only (this palette doesn't translate to dark mode — do not add a dark toggle)

